abstract: >
  Brasil CLI is a reproducible, auditable command-line interface and analysis
  toolkit for Brazilian public microdata (PNADC trimestral and anual visita 5,
  Censo 2022, TSE, IPCA, minimum-wage series). It produces labeled CSVs,
  SQLite databases, terminal dashboards with 95% bootstrap confidence
  intervals, and a bilingual interactive HTML data essay suitable for
  GitHub Pages. Designed for analysts, journalists, researchers, and
  LLM-driven agent workflows.
